Reduce memory from ~7 GB to ~500 MB: downscale PNGs, cache backgrounds, cap runtime image sizes

Fix 1 - Downscale source PNGs (optimize_pngs.py):
  - Directory-specific max dimensions (backgrounds 2048, frames 512, icons 256)
  - 360 PNGs resized, disk: 809 MB -> 76 MB, memory: 5631 MB -> 245 MB
  - Moved unused sub_screen/background_field.png and background_dark.png to _legacy/

Fix 2 - Cache shared images across screens:
  - MenuScreenMixin._chrome_cache: background + gold icon loaded once, shared by 5 screens
  - _MenuIconButton._shared_cache: stone + glow images loaded once for all icon buttons
  - LoginScreen._bg_cache: greyscale background shared with Client loading screen

Fix 3 - Runtime safety caps in image loaders:
  - FigureManager.load_image(): cap at 512px max dimension
  - SpellManager.load_image(): cap at 512px max dimension
  - BattleMoveManager._load_image(): cap at 512px max dimension
  - ScoreboardScroll: explicitly del raw surfaces after scaling glow rects
